day 2
#100 days of cybersecurity
To install Kali Linux on a windows maching using Virtual box, we need 3 things
1]Kali Linux VirtualBox Image
2]Oracle VirtualBox Software
3]7-Zip Tool (for extracting compressed files)

1]Install Oracle VirtualBox
Run the VirtualBox installer.
Grant Administrator permission when prompted.
In the setup wizard, click Next.
On the "Custom Setup" screen, just click Next (default settings are fine).
When the "Network Interface" warning shows up, click Yes.
If a "Missing Dependencies" message appears, click Yes again.
Click Install, then Finish after the installation completes.
2]download the virtual box software 
3]install 7-zip click install and close when your done.
set it up and then you are done
